create a new repository on github and upload from local -> follow instruction on github.com 

copy repository from github to local 
$ git clone https://github.com/angiebird/WSE_HW1.git

pull code from remote to local repository (use everytime before you push)
$ git pull

checkout the version from remote 
$ git checkout filename

check repository status
$ git status

add a new file to local repository
$ git add filename

add all file to local repository (the file type, names defined in .gitignore will not be added)
$ git add .

specify the file type/name which will not be committed 
$ vim .gitignore

remove a file from local repository
$ git rm filename

commit to local repository
$ git commit -m "I am comment"

push local repository to remote repository
$ git push


// ADVANCED 

see all the branches in this repository
$ git branch

create a new branch
$ git branch <branch_name>

switch to branch
$ git checkout <branch_name>

track a remote branch
$ git checkout --track origin/movieIndexer

check all remote repositories
$ git remote -v

untrack files
git rm --cache

// COLABORATION

fork the shared repository to your github -> press 'fork' on github.com

then clone to local

connect your local repository with original 
$ git remote add upstream https://github.com/original/Spoon-Knife.git 

pull from original repository
$ git pull upstream master

keep your master clean! -> create working branch (checkout '-b' will create branch if nothing to checkout)
$ git checkout -b <temp_branch> 

do some editing, add, commit and then
$ git push --set-upstream origin <new_branch_name>





// LESS USE

check commit log 
$ git log --graph

check difference with the head version
$ git diff HEAD

